page.title: 02THE SHORE LINE
page.content:
This is about the view from the {shoreline.
As you walk along the wall there are old{oyster beds }which are to the east of the Osea island causeway.The Osea causeway is not straight probably because there is harder rock underneath that may not have been straight and secondly so that the tide would not wash it away. The actual{seawall}itself is made of concrete slabs on top of a mound of earth which is about five metres high.On the mud there were a lot of gun cartridges that came from a wildfowl shooting club nearby. If you visit the area I think you should take a walk along the wall because it is very interesting,with plenty of things to see and do.
